<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS / SANTA MONICA: HOSPITAL TO OFFER FREE HEALTH AIDS FOR WOMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Women oversee their families' health care needs to such an extent, experts 
say, that they often forget to look after their own health. 
</P>
<P>
 To acknowledge that reality -- and to observe Mother's Day -- the Santa Monica 
Hospital Medical Center will offer an array of free health information and 
services for women this month at the Santa Monica Place shopping mall. 
</P>
<P>
 "We want to draw attention to the health of women, many of whom are the health 
care guardians of their families," said Ted Braun, the hospital's spokesman. 
"Many women are so busy, they forget about their own health." 
</P>
<P>
 The first public clinic, "Body, Mind, Spirit, a Celebration of Contemporary 
Women," will feature free blood pressure tests and screenings for skin cancer 
and other health problems. 
</P>
<P>
 At the clinic, to be held from noon to 4 p.m. Saturday at the mall's Center 
Court, information will be available on breast health, breast self-examination, 
nutrition, maternity and reproductive medicine. Nine female physicians will be 
on hand to answer questions. 
</P>
<P>
 Throughout this month the medical center will sponsor weekly seminars at the 
shopping mall and the hospital on such topics as "Women, HIV and AIDS: What Are 
the Odds?" and "Menopause: Beyond the Myths." Low-cost mammograms will also be 
offered.  
</P>
<P>
 For information on the free seminars or to make an appointment, call (800) 
922-0000. 
</P>
