<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: DIAMOND BAR ; COUNCILMAN'S VOTE ON DEVELOPMENT WAS OK, PROBE 
FINDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Fair Political Practices Commission has found no wrongdoing by Diamond Bar 
City Councilman Gary G. Miller in relation to charges that he had a financial 
interest in a proposed 170-acre commercial and residential development. 
</P>
<P>
 A commission investigation found that there was insufficient evidence to 
support a complaint filed by the Diamond Bar Citizens to Protect Country Living 
alleging that Miller participated in a vote affecting the proposed development 
while having a financial interest in it. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission said Miller did not violate conflict-of-interest laws when he 
voted on the general plan because by that time he had sold the property. 
</P>
