<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: THE REGION; WATER RECLAMATION PROJECT TO BEGIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Upper San Gabriel Valley Municipal Water District will join forces with 
the U.S. Bureau of Reclamation to develop a water reclamation project for the 
San Gabriel Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The project, which will reclaim water from the San Jose Creek Plant to be used 
to recharge the ground water basin and for irrigation, will be funded by a 
$500,000 matching grant from the federal government. 
</P>
<P>
 The grant will provide funds for pre-construction activities, including final 
design, engineering report, project management, public education and 
administrative costs. 
</P>
