<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLLYWOOD PARK; MIGRANT WORKER EQUALS MARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Migrant Worker overcame a slow start, wore down pacesetter Marmoe in 
mid-stretch and went on to win Wednesday's $46,000 feature race at Hollywood 
Park by three lengths. 
</P>
<P>
 Ridden by Chris Antley, Migrant Worker equaled the track record of 1:20 4/5 
for seven furlongs. 
</P>
<P>
 Migrant Worker lost a step at the start from the outside post but quickly 
recovered, stalking Marmoe until the early stretch and then taking command 
under Antley's urging. 
</P>
<P>
 Migrant Worker paid $4.40, $2.80 and $2.60 as the favorite in the field of 
eight older sprinters. Marmoe returned $4.80 and $3.40, and Juliannus paid 
$3.20 to show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
