<HEADLINE>
<P>
FLYING FINN SALLINEN VAULTS 16-4 3/4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Esa Sallinen of Burroughs High, a senior exchange student from Finland, 
cleared 16 feet 4 3/4 inches in the pole vault in the Foothill League track and 
field finals Wednesday at Birmingham High. 
</P>
<P>
 Taking advantage of a persistent tail wind, Sallinen cleared 13-0, 14-0, 15-0, 
16-0 and the magical -- for him -- five-meter height (16-4 3/4) on his first 
attempts before missing three times at 16-8. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is unbelievable," Sallinen said. "Five meters has been a big goal of 
mine for a long time. I've been chasing that mark for the last two years." 
</P>
<P>
 Sallinen, whose previous best was 16-0 1/4, moved to fourth on the all-time 
regional list and to second on this season's state list behind Scott Slover 
(17-0) of San Jose Leland High. 
</P>
<P>
 In other events, Hart's Jason Medearis won the 110-meter high hurdles (14.2 
seconds) and 300 intermediates (37.8), and Canyon's Mike Wenz won the 800 in a 
region-leading time of 1:54.4. JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</TEXT>
