<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; WINNING RUN SCORES FOR CHANNEL ISLANDS ON TWO-STRIKE BUNT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Channel Islands High pinch-runner Kenny Long scored the winning run from 
second base in the seventh inning Wednesday to lift the host Raiders to a 4-3 
Marmonte League victory over Camarillo. Long scored when Erik Jue misplayed 
Nacho Godinez's two-strike bunt. 
</P>
<P>
 The Raiders (15-8, 7-4 in league play) remain tied for second place with Simi 
Valley with three league games left. 
</P>
<P>
 Godinez (3-1) earned the victory in relief of starter Rene Sanchez, who had a 
no-hitter through 6 1/3 innings before giving up three runs on an error, a 
single and two doubles. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnny Olivares was perfect at the plate for Channel Islands with a single, a 
double and a triple. 
</P>
<P>
 Agoura 3, Royal 2 -- Charger Kevin Sass hit the decisive two-run home run in 
the sixth inning of the Marmonte League game at Royal (13-8, 6-5). Agoura 
pitcher Cary Gallardo (3-4) went the distance. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park 10, Westlake 3 -- Jeff Bennett hit a two-run home run to key the 
Panthers' five-run sixth inning that iced the Marmonte League game at Newbury 
Park (17-5, 10-1). Keith Smith (6-2) earned the complete-game victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame 6, St. Bernard 2 -- Jabbar Craigwell hit a two-run homer and Justin 
Bunch had a pair of doubles in four at-bats for visiting Notre Dame (15-5, 9-2) 
in the Mission League game. Senior left-hander Rich Igou (8-2) struck out seven 
and yielded three hits while recording his eighth complete game. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany 9, Loyola 2 -- Kris Yeamen's three-run home run snapped a 1-1 
third-inning tie and sent host Alemany to the Mission League victory.  
</P>
<P>
 Chaminade 2, Bishop Montgomery 1 -- Gabe Crecion's solo home run with one out 
in the bottom of the eighth carried host Chaminade (14-8, 6-5) to a Mission 
League victory -- the 10th in 13 games and setting a school record for 
victories in Division I play. 
</P>
<P>
 Birmingham 4, Monroe 3 -- Brave outfielder David Cohen tripled in the top of 
the eighth inning and scored the winning run on Lionel Villareal's two-out 
single in a Valley Pac-8 Conference game at Monroe.  
</P>
<P>
 Jamie Darnell (4-1) earned the victory in relief. COLLEGE SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 5-6, Bakersfield 0-0 -- Marcy James and Jana Kovar combined to hold 
visiting Bakersfield to one hit in a pair of makeup games from two separate 
rainouts. Moorpark is 29-12, 18-0. BOYS' TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
 Taft 15 1/2, Palisades 14 -- Toreador sophomore Dylan Mann and freshman Golan 
Sassoon each swept their four singles matches to lead Taft in a City Section 
4-A playoff semifinal at The Racquet Centre in Studio City. 
</P>
<P>
 Taft (14-0) will play University -- which defeated Chatsworth, 22-7 1/2, in 
the other semifinal -- for the City title next Tuesday.  
</P>
<P>
 Taft lost to Chatsworth in last year's championship. BOYS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Highland d. Littlerock, 15-7, 15-0, 15-1 -- Toby Sides made 18 assists for 
visiting Highland (13-0, 13-0), which clinched its first-ever league 
championship with a sweep of the Golden League match. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Millar had seven kills and Neal Scott added six more, while Mac Wilson 
made four blocks. 
</P>
