<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; HOMELESS 
ADVOCATES STILL OCCUPYING STRUCTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Homeless advocates, who illegally seized a vacant government-owned duplex in 
Los Angeles and set up a shelter for four homeless people, continued to occupy 
the structure Wednesday, pending negotiations with Housing and Urban 
Development officials. 
</P>
<P>
 Members of the California Homeless Network, who orchestrated the break-in 
Monday, say they plan to stay at the 17th Place duplex until they can reach an 
agreement with government officials to legally take over the structure. 
</P>
<P>
 Homeless advocates and HUD officials met Tuesday but did not reach a 
resolution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
