<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; PLAN TO PRIVATIZE FESTIVAL DELAYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A proposal to privatize the California Strawberry Festival by next year was 
stalled this week when members of the committee organizing the annual event 
were not present to address the Oxnard City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 The proposal would allow the city-funded California Strawberry Festival 
committee, which has organized the event for several years, to form a private 
corporation to administer the festival. 
</P>
<P>
 The plan is recommended for approval by James Faulconer, the city's recreation 
and community services director. 
</P>
<P>
 Although scheduled Tuesday on the council's consent agenda, which typically is 
reserved for non-controversial items, festival committee members had sought to 
address the council before the plan is considered. 
</P>
<P>
 The council rescheduled the matter to its May 17 meeting. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
