<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: VENICE; ANTI-GANG RALLY 
PLANNED IN OAKWOOD ON SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mothers who have lost children to violence are the focus of a peace rally 
scheduled for Saturday in the Oakwood section of Venice, the hub of a gang war 
believed responsible for the deaths of about 15 people since last summer. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilwoman Ruth Galanter will host the pre-Mother's Day event. Speakers will 
include anti-gang and other activists, along with relatives of people slain in 
gang violence around the county. The rally is scheduled to begin at 2 p.m. at 
the Oakwood Recreation Center, 767 California Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 A group from the neighborhood's Pearl White Theater is scheduled to perform. 
</P>
<P>
 For information on the rally, call (310) 524-1150. 
</P>
