<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: MEMBERS SOUGHT FOR EDUCATION PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Asian Pacific American Education Commission of the Los Angeles Unified 
School District is seeking parents, students, professionals and community 
members interested in applying for one of four vacancies on the commission. 
</P>
<P>
 The panel is one of seven appointed by the Board of Education to serve in an 
ombudsman role for the various ethnic groups represented by students and 
district employees. 
</P>
<P>
 Carmencita Davino, director of the commission office, said they are looking 
for people who are interested in working to improve educational opportunities 
for Asian Pacific American students. Candidates should also be able to 
represent the commission at school and community functions, and serve as a 
liaison between the schools and community. 
</P>
<P>
 There is a particular need for representation from the San Fernando Valley, 
Davino said. 
</P>
<P>
 Commissioners are required to attend one evening meeting a month and be 
available for other duties. They serve a two-year term on a voluntary basis. 
For information, call (213) 625-6796. KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
