EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; MAN DIES OF INJURIES AFTER 2 CARS 
COLLIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 43-year-old Simi Valley man died after he made a left turn in front of an 
oncoming car, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Thorne Gardner was pronounced dead of multiple injuries at Simi Valley 
Hospital at 9:55 p.m. Tuesday, about an hour after the accident, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Gardner was turning left onto Stow Street from Los Angeles Avenue 
when he was struck by a car driven by Tina Cammarello, who was traveling east 
on Los Angeles Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Cammarello, 39, of Simi Valley had some back pain but declined to be 
hospitalized, police said. Her passenger, Roland Tinoco, 40, of Woodland Hills, 
also had back pain and declined immediate treatment. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said they do not know how fast the two vehicles were traveling when 
they collided. The speed limit on Los Angeles Avenue is 45 m.p.h. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators will check the vehicles to see if either was malfunctioning, and 
the Ventura County coroner's office is running tests to see if Gardner was 
intoxicated or impaired at the time of the accident, Simi Valley Police Sgt. 
Jeff Malgren said. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
