<P>
INDIA EXPLOSION KILLS 23 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fireworks exploded in a warehouse in western India on Wednesday, killing at 
least 23 people and injuring 77. 
</P>
<P>
 The explosion occurred after midnight as Hindus set off firecrackers during a 
religious procession. One of them landed in the warehouse in Chikhalthane 
village, about 730 miles southwest of New Delhi. 
</P>
