<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA050594-0245 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 038795 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
May 5, 1994, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 2; Column 2; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
225 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND HOME PRICES, SALES DROP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sales of existing homes in Southern California dipped in the first quarter of 
1994 but were up sharply compared to the first quarter of 1993. Prices in most 
areas continued to erode. 
</P>
<P>
 Statewide, sales were up slightly on an annualized basis.  
</P>
<P>
