<P>
 Times Mirror Unit Buys Publisher: Mosby-Year Book, a unit of Times Mirror Co., 
said it has acquired Great Performance, a publisher of educational materials to 
promote consumer and employee health, for an undisclosed price.Mosby-Year Book, 
based in St. Louis, is a leading publisher in health science. Great 
Performance, based in Portland, Ore., has 48 employees and posted 1993 revenue 
of about $5 million. Its name will be changed to Mosby-Great Performance, and 
Mark J. Tager, a physician who founded Great Performance, will remain as 
president. Los Angeles-based Times Mirror is a diversified publishing and 
information company that publishes the Los Angeles Times, Newsday and New York 
Newsday newspapers. 
