<P>
 Mexico's Unemployment at 3.8% in January: The nation's jobless rate was up 0.4 
percentage point from the year-ago period, according to a report from the 
government-owned Instituto Nacional de Estadistica Geografia e Informatica, or 
Inegi. Inegi said 55% of the country's population age 12 or older was 
economically active in January. It also said 32% of Mexico's working population 
received a daily income of one to two times the country's minimum wage of 
$4.30. 
