<HEADLINE>
<P>
INDOOR SOCCER TEAM NAMES FIRST COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Splash, Anaheim's new entry in the Continental Indoor Soccer League, has 
named George Fernandez coach for the 1994 season. 
</P>
<P>
 Fernandez is a nine-year veteran of the defunct Major Soccer League, playing 
with the Cleveland Crunch, the San Diego Sockers and the Los Angeles Lazers. He 
is coming off a season as captain and assistant coach with the Crunch, which 
won the 1993-94 National Professional Soccer League title. 
</P>
<P>
 Fernandez led Cleveland's defense with 91 blocked shots and scored nine goals 
with 12 assists. He will not play for the Splash. 
</P>
<P>
 Fernandez was most valuable player in the 1990 Major Indoor Soccer League 
all-star game and has won four indoor championships, three with the Sockers and 
one with the Crunch. 
</P>
