<HEADLINE>
<P>
DISNEY CRUISES INTO NEW VENTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mickey and Donald are taking to the sea in the Walt Disney Co.'s latest 
venture: building and operating a line of vacation cruise ships. 
</P>
<P>
 Disney will build two vessels that will offer island-hopping vacations and 
on-board children's activities featuring Disney characters, the company 
confirmed this week. 
</P>
<P>
 Disney said months ago that it was considering such a move. But a formal 
announcement on Tuesday was coupled with news that it hired Crystal Cruises 
President Arthur Rodney to oversee development and operation of the new 
project. 
</P>
<P>
 "Operating our own cruise line will allow us to bring a new dimension of 
entertainment to our guests," said Michael D. Eisner, Disney's chairman. "We 
are creating a distinctive Disney product, with recognized Disney quality and 
service, in this popular and growing vacation segment." 
</P>
<P>
 Disney plans to make both of its ships large enough to carry 2,400 passengers. 
The first is expected to be launched by 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
