<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSBITES / ANNE MICHAUD: GETTING CAUGHT IN THE MOM-ENTUM OF THE DAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNE MICHAUD, Anne Michaud is a staff writer for The Times Orange County 
Edition. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Mezzanine Restaurant will host Mystery Cafe players Sunday for a 
performance of the "Zodiac Club," an audience-participation mystery set in a 
1920s speak-easy. 
</P>
<P>
 Diners are invited to join in solving the mystery or just sit back and enjoy 
the show. 
</P>
<P>
 On the menu are spinach and crab meat salad, turkey breast with mushroom sauce 
and an ice cream truffle with raspberry sauce. The children's menu is a green 
salad, chicken fingers, fries and an ice cream bar. Doors open at 11:30 a.m., 
and brunch begins at noon. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $49 for adults (tax and tip included) and $29 for children under 
16. 
</P>
<P>
 19800 MacArthur Blvd., Irvine. (800) 953-2583. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Strolling musicians, family portraits and a visit by a Power Ranger are the 
highlights of a Sunday Mother's Day brunch at the Hyatt Newporter. Baby-sitting 
is provided. 
</P>
<P>
 The hotel's plaza and patio areas will be set up for a buffet brunch from 
10:30 a.m. to 3 p.m. that includes seafood, made-to-order omelets, salads, meat 
from a carving station, fruit, champagne and dessert. 
</P>
<P>
 The price is $27.95, $23.95 for seniors, $13.95 for children under 12. There 
is no charge for youngsters under 3. Prices do not include tax. 
</P>
<P>
 1107 Jamboree Road, Newport Beach. (714) 729-1234, Ext. 582. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Gandhi is offering a champagne buffet brunch on Mother's Day from 11 a.m. to 
2:30 p.m. The menu includes tandoori chicken, seekh kebab, vegetable samosa and 
several other Indian dishes. 
</P>
<P>
 The price is $12.95 for adults, $6.95 for children under 5, plus tax and tip. 
</P>
<P>
 1621-D Sunflower Ave., South Coast Plaza Village, Santa Ana. (714) 556-7273. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Moms who dine at Carmelo's on Sunday from 5 p.m. to 12:30 a.m. will receive a 
free Italian dessert and a long-stemmed rose. In addition, beginning about 6:30 
p.m., pianist Maurizio Metalli will perform with guitar duo Tim & Mike, who 
take their inspiration from Simon & Garfunkel. 
</P>
<P>
 3520 E. Pacific Coast Highway, Corona del Mar. (714) 675-1922. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Brunch at the Westin South Coast Plaza hotel on Sunday comes complete with an 
orchid for Mom and a 20% discount card for a visit to the Jose Eber salon at 
South Coast Plaza. 
</P>
<P>
 The buffet, served in the hotel's Garden Court Cafe from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m., 
includes rack of lamb, roasted turkey breast, hot appetizers, seven kinds of 
salad, chocolate-dipped strawberries and pastry. 
</P>
<P>
 The cost is $28 for adults and $14 for children ages 6 to 12. There is no 
charge for children 5 and under. 
</P>
<P>
 686 Anton Blvd., Costa Mesa. (714) 662-6694. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Black Sheep Bistro will hold its fifth annual fund-raiser on Sunday for 
the City of Hope Cancer Research Center in Duarte. 
</P>
<P>
 A $25 prix fixe menu includes assorted Spanish tapas, a green salad and a 
choice of linguine pomodoro , chicken with herb garlic sauce or venison chops. 
For dessert, there are fresh berries or an Italian sundae. 
</P>
<P>
 A la carte entrees are $8 and include chicken salad, shrimp sandwich, breast 
of chicken with spicy cilantro sauce, sausage and peppers with spinach 
fettuccine and loin of lamb. 
</P>
<P>
 Hours are 11 a.m. to 2 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 303 El Camino Real, Tustin. (714) 544-6060. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Mrs. Gooch's, an upscale grocer and natural-foods store, is planning to open 
its first Orange County location in the fall. The grocer has seven stores in 
the L.A. area. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said it plans to locate in the Tustin Courtyard, off Newport 
Avenue in Tustin. 
</P>
