COMMUNITY NEWS: LONG BEACH: ANOTHER FIRE SETS BACK REOPENING OF BALLROOM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two days before it was scheduled to reopen after a fire, the International 
Grand Ballroom was hit by another blaze that will keep the facility closed for 
another four to six months. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire in the ballroom attic late Friday was probably caused by faulty 
wiring, said Long Beach Fire Department spokesman Randy Grimm.Damages were 
estimated at $150,000. No injuries were reported, but 25 residents in an 
apartment building next door were evacuated. 
</P>
<P>
 The ballroom interior was damaged in an October fire. That blaze, which caused 
$40,000 in damage, was traced to a malfunctioning commercial refrigerator, said 
Ed McMahon, who has owned the downtown facility on East 1st Street for 22 
years. 
</P>
<P>
 The ballroom, which opened in 1956, has been used for wedding receptions and 
private parties in recent years, McMahon said. 
